<TITLE> BCB XI-SA warm-up match end in a tie </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Chittagong, March 7 (bdnews24.com)The warm-up match between BCB XI and South Africa ended in a dramatic tie after the visitors levelled the match at 243-8. Chasing a target of 243, South Africa could manage only four runs while it needed five runs in the 5oth over to win the game. Earlier, Bangladesh set the target losing seven wickets. South African skipper Graeme Smith scored the highest 70 runs while AB Morkel added 57 to cruise the team to the corner of victory. The team fell apart after it quickly lost two wickets in the final over. None of the Bangladeshi players could reach a half century but a concerted contribution added up to the team total. Opener Junaed Siddique faced the first ball to be out without a run. Mahmudullah Riyad was the top scorer with 37 not out while Rakibul smashed 33, Shakib Al Hasan 32, Tamim Iqbal 30 and Naim Islam 30. Mosharraf Hosssain Rubel claimed three wickets conceding only 19 runs. Bangladesh will face South Africa in the opening ODI of the 3-match series Sunday. bdnews
